text: The best steaks we‚Äôve had in a long time. Sauces also delicious, just a fab meal all round. Great wines and not overpriced. Staff are fun and friendly - our server Ron was great and very kind as he organised a welcome plate for us!

Ordered online, was informed delivery would take approximately 1 hour. No problem. Also aware it is Valentine's Day, so allowed for a  natural delay. 1h30mins later I send the restaurant a message. They reply not to worry, food is on its way. No problem. 2 hours now have passed, they tell me the delivery driver has had an accident. They can either refund me or re-send. They are unapologetic, it is leave it or take it.  I re-order, as we are hungry (it is 10pm) and I paid a ridiculous AED450 for our meal. Food arrives over 3 hours after my initial order. It is cold, badly packed. Steak is dry. Crab cakes broken (and cold). Caesar salad is soggy, packed in its dressing. Restaurant didn't even have the decency to send me, say, a slice of cake, or a "sorry for the inconvenience." I find it hard to believe in the accident story. Or maybe there was an accident and they delivered the same food cooked 2 hours before. Who knows. They did say "Happy Valentines Day" over whatsupp though. Guess that is supposed to be enough.

I had been wanting to go to Couqley for a while now and it met all my expectations! 
We tried a LOT of food, but from the starters we had I have to say the foie gras and the po√™l√©e de champignons were my favorites. For the main we had the sea bass and the magret de canard, which were both excellent although I would have preferred the duck to be in the oven a little longer (will specify next time). The sides we had were also delicious: amazing pur√©e with truffles, spinach in cream, and portobello mushrooms were all delicious.

Another very pleasant surprise: the wine! We had a Merlot from Chile and it was AMAZING and very reasonably priced!!! Highly recommended!

The service was also great, and our waiter Duncan was very attentive and friendly, and then manager came by the table to ask if all was in place.

All in all, exactly what I expected, a wonderful experience with great French food (this is coming from a French girl who is a total foodie)!

Finally a real french bistro opened in dubai!

I tried Couqley for the first time last night and I have to say it was the best dining experience I had in dubai for a long time. 

From the decor to the food and the friendly but professional staff, It feels like, when passing through the door, you jumped straight  from dubai to paris most authentic brasserie.

The wine isn't overpriced like in all other restaurant here in dubai (a bottle of Bordeaux at 95aed, what else do you need), the food is great, especially the steak frite served with a tasty secret sauce and the pain perdu , oh my god, I still dream of it! A thick caramelized brioche covered with salted caramel sauce and served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream: just amazing!

I will definately go back and recommend it to my friends, thank you Couqley !
